items.title: generate_access_token can't use service_account_path format

labels.name: api: iam
labels.description: Issues related to the Cloud IAM API.

labels.name: type: question
labels.description: Request for information or clarification. Not an issue.

items.body:
According to the docstring for `generate_access_token`, `service_account_path` can be used to build the required format for a service account:
```python
client = iam_credentials_v1.IAMCredentialsClient()
name = client.service_account_path('[PROJECT]', '[SERVICE_ACCOUNT]')
scope = []
response = client.generate_access_token(name, scope)
```

But `service_account_path` returns a format that the IAM API doesn't accept:

```python
>>> print(name)
projects/[PROJECT]/serviceAccounts/[SERVICE_ACCOUNT]
```

The correct format is: `projects/-/serviceAccounts/[ACCOUNT_EMAIL_OR_UNIQUEID]`  I don't know if all service account API endpoints accept this format.
